### What are firewalls for?
Firewall secures the server by monitoring incoming and out going traffic. Each server should have an it own firewall

### Why is the traffic served over HTTPS
HTTPS is a secure protocol which allows data to exchanged more securely between the server and the client and vice versa

### What monitoring is used for?
Monitoring server consistently to quickly identify threat to it operation  and proactively engabge the threat

### How the monitoring tool is collecting data?
Monitoring tool such as sumologic or others collects data on server performance and records it

### Explain what to do if you want to monitor your web server QPS
Monitoring tool monitors the numbers of queries per seconds on the web server 

Terminating SSL at the load balancer exposes the decrypted data. Traffic should be encrypted end-to-end

Single MySQL server handling write operation is a single point of failure (SPOF). Write operation should be load balanced across multiple databases

Uniformity in server component should be avoided as this may lead to vulnerability of the entire system